                   feeds tcc a .cpp file. Upstream 0.9.27 classifies that by
                   extension as a binary object and rejects it ("unrecognized
                   file type"), aborting the C-only build though no C++ is ever
                   compiled. Treating it as C source under -E lets `tcc -E`
                   satisfy the probe with no -x c hack. */
                filetype = AFF_TYPE_C;
            else
                flags |= AFF_TYPE_BIN;
